upports `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_MAINTAINER_MODE=skills,plugins`, but the committed runtime config note still tells maintainers to set `=true` and says the launcher forces all five INDEX_* flags. The same stale note appears in .claude/mcp.json:71 and .codex/config.toml:99, and the install guide repeats the all-five wording at .opencode/skills/system-code-graph/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:235-241.","evidence":".opencode/bin/mk-code-index-launcher.cjs:76-83 documents/implements true vs comma-list category resolution; .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:280 documents the new comma-subset behavior; opencode.json:83, .claude/mcp.json:71, and .codex/config.toml:99 still only describe true forcing all five categories.","recommendation":"Update the runtime config notes and install guide to describe comma subsets, and avoid directing maintainers to the old all-five-only path unless full coverage is intentionally desired."},{"id":"N2","severity":"P1","file":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/rename-invariants.vitest.ts","line":"63","title":"Skill-advisor rename tests still assert the legacy disable variable","why":"The config invariant test reads the current runtime configs and expects `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED`, but current configs contain only `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED`. That makes the test stale/red by inspection and also leaves the canonical MK disable path untested in the handler/hook suites.","evidence":"rename-invariants.vitest.ts:63-66 asserts `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED`; opencode.json:56, .claude/mcp.json:45, and .codex/config.toml:109 set `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED`; advisor-recommend.vitest.ts:356-358 and claude-user-prompt-submit-hook.vitest.ts:106-107 only exercise the legacy name.","recommendation":"Change tests to assert MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED as canonical, add explicit legacy-alias tests only if legacy support is still intended, and cover native MCP handler plus Claude/Codex hook paths."},{"